    notes: "DC = guaranteed polymerization at depth where light cannot reach (deep post canals, opaque restorations). Fluoride release at the core-dentin interface provides secondary caries protection under crown margins. Automix cartridge = consistent ratio, no hand-mixing variability.",
    steps: ["Apply Clearfil SE Bond 2 or Clearfil Universal Bond Quick 2 to prepared dentin","If using fiber post: treat post surface (sandblast → silane) → coat with DC Core Plus","Inject DC Core Plus into canal around post and/or onto preparation","Allow self-cure component to initiate (especially in deep areas)","Light-cure accessible surfaces 20–40 sec","Wait 4–5 min total for full DC set before prep","Prep core to final crown preparation dimensions"],
